  "prompt": "Can I make a voice call from my iPad using Jio SIM?",
  "response": "You cannot make traditional voice calls directly from an iPad using a Jio SIM, as iPads do not support traditional cellular voice calling features like a smartphone. However, if your iPad has cellular capabilities (iPad models that support a SIM card), you can still use it for voice calls through internet-based services. Here are a couple of options:\n\n1. **FaceTime**: If both you and the person you're calling have Apple devices, you can use FaceTime for voice and video calls over Wi-Fi or cellular data.\n\n2. **Third-Party Apps**: You can use apps like WhatsApp, Skype, Zoom, or Google Duo to make voice calls. These apps require an internet connection but can work over Wi-Fi or cellular data.\n\n3. **iPhone Cellular Calling**: If you have an iPhone, you can enable \"Calls on Other Devices\" to make and receive iPhone calls on your iPad as long as both devices are signed into the same Apple ID and connected to the same Wi-Fi network.\n\nRemember to check your data plan, as using cellular data for calls may incur charges depending on your plan.",
